   "source": [
    "# Full example\n",
    "\n",
    "This example demonstrates the power of the `rapbro` interface to Google Earth Engine (GEE) to collect many subbasin attributes associated with multiple coordinate pairs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "93516826-74e4-4cdb-95a5-39706bb8b89a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import contextily as cx\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import rabpro\n",
    "from rabpro.subbasin_stats import Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "197eb567-f163-494c-9479-d140814ce8fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First let's create a list of coordinate pairs that we'll use to delineate our basins of interest. For this example, we'll retrieve the subbasins associated with dams in Sri Lanka."
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "vdams_srilanka = pd.read_csv(\"vote-dams_sri-lanka.csv\")\n",
    "coord_list = [\n",
    "    (vdams_srilanka.iloc[i][\"lat\"], vdams_srilanka.iloc[i][\"long\"])\n",
    "    for i in range(0, vdams_srilanka.shape[0])\n",
    "]\n",
    "vdams_srilanka.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d56356e8-a0ed-4974-8ad8-44ba5359a5e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if not os.path.exists(\"basins_sl.gpkg\"):\n",
    "    basins_sl = []\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(coord_list)):\n",
    "        print(i)\n",
    "        # i = 0\n",
    "        rpo = rabpro.profiler(coord_list[i], force_merit=True, verbose=False)\n",
    "        rpo.delineate_basins()\n",
    "        basins_sl.append(rpo.basins)\n",
    "\n",
    "    basins_sl = pd.concat(basins_sl)\n",
    "    basins_sl.to_file(\"basins_sl.gpkg\", driver=\"GPKG\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    basins_sl = gpd.read_file(\"basins_sl.gpkg\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee472c6a-77a1-405b-8357-6f363b386176",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We need to upload our basin vector layer as a GEE asset because it too large to send as a json payload. This can be done manually through the GEE code editor or via `rabpro` automation. This automation requires that you have a writeable Google Cloud Platform (GCP) bucket and that you are authenticated via the command-line to call the `gsutil` and `earthengine` programs. These programs enable sending files to GCP and onward to GEE respectively."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b4539f74-da5a-4405-a799-03d6acac6215",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "import config\n",
    "gcp_bucket = config.gcp_bucket\n",
    "gee_user = config.gee_user\n",
    "zip_path = rabpro.utils.build_gee_vector_asset(basins_sl, \"basins_sl.zip\")\n",
    "your_gee_asset = rabpro.utils.upload_gee_vector_asset(\n",
    "    zip_path, gee_user, gcp_bucket, gee_folder=\"rabpro\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a07ce6b-4645-49b1-b2ff-39af540367fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next let's define a list of Google Earth Engine (GEE) datasets to intersect with our delineated basins:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "5aaff7f7-131a-4f72-9a71-981d651fa072",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_list = [\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"JRC/GSW1_3/GlobalSurfaceWater\",\n",
    "        \"occurrence\",\n",
    "        time_stats=[\"median\"],\n",
    "        stats=[\"mean\"],\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"ECMWF/ERA5_LAND/MONTHLY\",\n",
    "        \"temperature_2m\",\n",
    "        time_stats=[\"median\"],\n",
    "        stats=[\"mean\"],\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"UCSB-CHG/CHIRPS/DAILY\", \"precipitation\", time_stats=[\"median\"], stats=[\"mean\"]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ab60a65b-dc0d-493f-8b7f-8a2070a46fc8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's do the intersection with `rabpro.subbasin_stats.main`, format the results, and join it to our basins GeoDataFrame."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "7600a0c1-0344-4a45-9fbe-dede27ae2d60",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "your_gee_asset = 'users/jstacompute/basins_sl'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "3fa177f6-9037-42e0-946d-44a6c9286d3e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if not os.path.exists(\"res.gpkg\"):\n",
    "    urls, tasks = rabpro.subbasin_stats.main(\n",
    "        dataset_list, gee_feature_path=your_gee_asset, folder=\"rabpro\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    tag_list = [\"wateroccur\", \"temperature_2m\", \"precip\"]\n",
    "    data = rabpro.subbasin_stats.format_gee(urls, tag_list)\n",
    "\n",
    "    res = gpd.GeoDataFrame(pd.concat([data, basins_sl], axis=1))\n",
    "    res = res.set_geometry(\"geometry\")\n",
    "    res.to_file(\"res.gpkg\", driver=\"GPKG\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    res = gpd.read_file(\"res.gpkg\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2b466ebc-6c42-40b4-8b1a-5ba6e0c0d134",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, a visualization!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "b40c3e25-9029-4461-9191-c0007df0c50e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def build_panel(col_name, col_label, axis):\n",
    "    axis.set_xlim([left-0.5, right+0.5])\n",
    "    axis.set_ylim([bot-0.2, top+0.2])\n",
    "    axis.set_axis_off()\n",
    "    res.plot(\n",
    "        ax=axis,\n",
    "        column=col_name,\n",
    "        legend=True,\n",
    "        legend_kwds={\"label\": col_label, \"orientation\": \"horizontal\"},\n",
    "    )    \n",
    "    cx.add_basemap(axis, zoom=10, crs=res.crs, attribution=\"\")\n",
    "    return axis\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "left, bot, right, top = res.total_bounds\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "ax = [\n",
    "    build_panel(col_name, col_label, ax[i])\n",
    "    for col_name, col_label, i in zip(\n",
    "        [x for x in res.columns[0:3]],\n",
    "        [\"Water occurence %\", \"Temperature (K)\", \"Precipitation (mm/day)\"],\n",
    "        range(0, 3),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "]"
   ]
  }
 ],
